title: Jonas Motiejūnas (rower)
text: Jonas Motiejūnas (Russian name: Йонас Матеюнас; born 21 September 1940) is a Soviet <a href="Rowing%20%28sport%29">rower</a> from Lithuania. He competed at the <a href="1964%20Summer%20Olympics">1964 Summer Olympics</a> in <a href="Tokyo">Tokyo</a> with the men's coxed four where they came seventh.
